<font size="3" color="red">Searching and Updating</font>

At the top right of the page is a search box.  Enter a search string here to search for either an application's name, author's name, repository name, or description<br><br>

The <input type='button' value='Update Applications'> button forces an update of all available applications.  Community Applications normally downloads the updated application lists whenever entering it loads.  However, there is a delay of up to two hours before a new application may appear on the feed.  If you know that a new application is available, but it is not appearing, then you should Update the Applications if you want to use that particular application.

<hr>

<font size='3' color='red'>Installed / Previously Installed Applications</font>

By selecting <input type='button' value='Installed Apps'></input> will display all applications which are currently installed, and allow you to edit them.
A <img src='/plugins/dynamix.docker.manager/images/remove.png' width='20px'></img> will appear next to the application.  Selecting this will allow you to uninstall the application, and optionally delete the appdata folder for the application (See <b>Settings</b> section)<br><br>

By selecting <input type='button' value='Previous Apps'></input> will display all applications which have been previously installed, and allow you to re-install them.
A <img src='/plugins/dynamix.docker.manager/images/remove.png' width='20px'></img> will appear next to the application.  Selecting this will remove (ie: delete the user template) from the list of previously installed applications<br><br>
