<font size='3' color='red'>Resource Monitor</font>

The resource monitor will display some statistics on the currently running docker applications (% CPU, % Memory, Network Utilization).  Additionally, it will also calculate the size of the various application's appData.

It also features cAdvisor integration.  If the cAdvisor application is not currently installed, a direct link to install it will be present (highly recommended to install it).  Once installed, clicking on each application's icon will take you directly to cAdvisor's page for that application which will display even more useful information about the application.

<font size="3" color="red">Advanced - dockerHub Integration</font>


There is a setting which you can enable which will allow you to search dockerHub for other applications beyond the ones which have had unRaid templates created for them.

When this option is enabled, a few more options are available.

<li>Clicking on the Application's Name of any application will then search dockerHub for that application.
<li>After performing any search for applications, a button will appear (<input type='button' value='Get more results from dockerHub' style='margin:0px'>) to then allow you to search dockerHub for that application.

Within the dockerHub search results, you can navigate and search as before.  Clicking the author's name will search for all applications from that author.  Clicking the application's name will search for more results for that application name.

Clicking <input type='button' value='Add'> will attempt to create a template for that application and install it.  There are however some caveats with regards to the conversion process.  See this thread for more details: <a href='http://lime-technology.com/forum/index.php?topic=40262.msg401570#msg401570' target='_blank'>http://lime-technology.com/forum/index.php?topic=40262.msg401570#msg401570</a>

At a later time if you wish to manage the application added (Edit / restore to defaults, etc), the application will be available under the UNCATEGORIZED category.  (Alternatively, you could categorize the plugin by using the Docker Categorizer plugin <a href='http://lime-technology.com/forum/index.php?topic=40111.0'>HERE</a>

Depending upon what search term is currently being used, Community Applications may also offer you some alternate search terms for more relevant containers.

<strong>NOTE:</strong> When adding an application from dockerHub, popups must be enabled within your browser

